              How's the low-light performance vs Sony A7 IV?
            </button>
          </h3>
          <div class="faq-answer" style="max-height: 0; overflow: hidden;">
            <p>Slightly better. The S5 II maxes at ISO 204,800 (vs 102,400 on A7 IV) and produces cleaner files at high ISOs. The dual native ISO design (ISO 640 and 4000) means noise is minimal at common video ISOs. For nighttime event shooting, the S5 II has an edge.</p>
          </div>
